{"word":"πτερωτός","slug":"πτερωτός","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>πτερωτός</b></el> <el>(πτερωτός, ή, όν) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:πτερόω'><el>πτερόω</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>feathered</i>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><i>winged</i>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Tragic, in Tragic Greek'>Trag.</a></b>; so, <el>πτ. φθόγγος</el>, a sound <i>as of wings</i>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><el>πτερωτοί</el> (<a href='S:scilicet'>sc.</a> <el>ὄρνιθες</el>) <i>feathered fowl, birds</i>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}